The theorem `h_lamb_gt_q_sub_one` is a helper lemma that shows for a primitive root of unity `lamb` of order `n`, and a natural number `q`, that `‚Äñeval (‚Üëq) (X - C lamb)‚Äñ > q - 1`. This lemma is likely used in the main proof to establish some inequality involving roots of unity.

Let's look at how to prove this lemma.

The expression `(X - (C lamb)).eval (q : ‚ÑÇ)` evaluates to `q - lamb`. So we need to show that `‚Äñq - lamb‚Äñ > q - 1`.

Since `lamb` is a primitive root of unity of order `n`, we know that `lamb` is on the unit circle, so `‚Äñlamb‚Äñ = 1`. Also, `q` is a natural number, so `q ‚â• 0`.

The triangle inequality tells us that `‚Äñq - lamb‚Äñ ‚â• |q - ‚Äñlamb‚Äñ|`. Since `‚Äñlamb‚Äñ = 1`, we have `‚Äñq - lamb‚Äñ ‚â• |q - 1|`.

If `q ‚â• 1`, then `|q - 1| = q - 1`, so `‚Äñq - lamb‚Äñ ‚â• q - 1`. Since `lamb ‚âÝ 1` (from `h_lamb`), we have `q - lamb ‚âÝ q - 1` (because `lamb ‚âÝ 1`), so the inequality is strict: `‚Äñq - lamb‚Äñ > q - 1`.

If `q = 0`, then `‚Äñ0 - lamb‚Äñ = ‚Äñ-lamb‚Äñ = ‚Äñlamb‚Äñ = 1`. We need to show `1 > 0 - 1 = -1`. This is true since `1 > -1`.

So the lemma holds. Let's formalize this in Lean.

