Next, we have the lemma `le_abs_of_dvd` which is a helper lemma for working with absolute values and divisibility:

```tactics
lemma le_abs_of_dvd {i j : ‚Ñ§} (gj: 0 ‚âÝ j) (h: i ‚à£ j) : |i| ‚â§ |j| := by
  rcases h with ‚ü®c, h‚ÇÄ‚ü©
  rcases em (c = 0) with hc | h
  ¬∑ by_contra
    rw [hc, mul_zero] at h‚ÇÄ
    exact gj h‚ÇÄ.symm
  ¬∑ calc
      |i| = |i| * 1 := by simp
      _ ‚â§ |i| * |c| := by gcongr 1; exact Int.one_le_abs h
      _ = |i * c| := (abs_mul i c).symm
      _ = |j| := by rw [h‚ÇÄ.symm]
```

This lemma is establishing that if $i$ divides $j$ and $j \neq 0$, then $|i| \leq |j|$. The proof proceeds by cases: if $c = 0$, then $j = 0$, which contradicts $j \neq 0$. Otherwise, $|i| \leq |i \cdot c| = |j|$.

