This defines $\phi(n)$ as the $n$-th cyclotomic polynomial with integer coefficients. 

Next, we have a lemma stating that the $n$-th cyclotomic polynomial divides $X^n - 1$:

```tactics
lemma phi_dvd (n : ‚Ñï) : phi n ‚à£ X ^ n - 1 := by
  rw [phi]
