The norm `‚Äñq - lamb‚Äñ` is the modulus of the complex number `q - lamb`. If `q` is a natural number, then `q` is a real number, so `q - lamb` is a complex number with real part `q - lamb.re` and imaginary part `-lamb.im`. 

